sequenceDiagram
autonumber

box rgb(230, 244, 255) Backend
participant FE as Browser UI
participant API as Backend API
participant CC as ComplianceController
participant OS as OAuthService
participant FC as framework-controls.json
participant CHK as checks.json
participant STR as ToolExecutionStrategy
participant RES as ToolResolver
participant MAP as tool-name-mapping.json
participant MCP as Backend McpClient
participant RFC as REST Fallback Client
participant RTC as rest-tool-contracts.json
participant RN as ResponseNormalizer
participant EE as EvaluationEngine
participant RF as ReportFormatter
participant ERC as EvidenceReportCollector
end

box rgb(255, 247, 230) Client
participant OP as Provider OAuth Page
end

box rgb(232, 255, 242) MCP Servers
participant GHM as GitHub MCP Server
participant GLM as GitLab MCP Server
participant BBM as Bitbucket MCP Server
end

participant PRA as Provider REST APIs

Note over FE: Browser connects provider (OAuth)
FE->>API: GET /api/auth/{provider}/connect
API-->>FE: Redirect to provider authorization URL
FE->>OP: Authorize app access
OP-->>API: Callback with code/state
API->>OS: Exchange code and store token
OS-->>API: Token stored

Note over FE: Browser starts compliance run
FE->>API: POST /api/compliance/evaluate-standard
API->>CC: evaluateStandard(request)
CC->>OS: getAccessToken(provider, tenant)
OS-->>CC: Access token
CC->>FC: Load controls for ISO27001
FC-->>CC: control_id + check_ids
CC->>CHK: Load checks by check_id
CHK-->>CC: canonical tool + evaluation_logic

loop each repository and control
  loop each check in control
    CC->>STR: executeTool(provider, canonicalToolName, params)
    STR->>MCP: listTools(provider)
    MCP-->>STR: mcpExposedTools

    STR->>RES: resolve(provider, canonicalToolName, mcpExposedTools, preference)
    RES->>MAP: read provider mapping for canonical tool
    MAP-->>RES: mcpToolName + restToolName
    RES-->>STR: selected mode + mapped tool name

    alt mode = mcp
      STR->>MCP: callTool(provider, mapped mcpToolName, params)
      alt provider = github
        MCP->>GHM: JSON-RPC tools/call
        GHM-->>MCP: Raw MCP evidence
      else provider = gitlab
        MCP->>GLM: JSON-RPC tools/call
        GLM-->>MCP: Raw MCP evidence
      else provider = bitbucket
        MCP->>BBM: JSON-RPC tools/call
        BBM-->>MCP: Raw MCP evidence
      end
      MCP-->>STR: Evidence payload
    else mode = rest
      STR->>RFC: callTool(provider, mapped restToolName, params)
      RFC->>RTC: load rest tool contract
      RTC-->>RFC: method + path + query + body template
      RFC->>PRA: Execute provider REST request
      PRA-->>RFC: Raw REST evidence
      RFC-->>STR: Evidence payload
    end

    STR->>RN: normalizeEvidence(payload)
    RN-->>STR: Standardized evidence
    STR-->>CC: Evidence + execution metadata

    CC->>EE: evaluate(check logic, evidence)
    EE-->>CC: Check verdict
  end

  CC->>CC: Aggregate check verdicts to control PASS/FAIL/ERROR
end

CC->>RF: format report block
RF-->>CC: Formatted report section
CC->>ERC: collect and write evidence report JSON
ERC-->>CC: file_name + download_url
CC-->>API: Final compliance result
API-->>FE: JSON response + evidence_report link
Note over FE: UI renders results table and report link
